race.comment: Tricky maiden but it might be the right setup for LIGHT THE NIGHT (8), who looks as though he will appreciate the rise to 1200m. He's drawn wide so he may have to concede a bit of a start but the track is often conducive to backmarkers. MOSTLY FOR SHOW (9) has placed in three of his six career starts. This is a much easier assignment than the 3YO race he contested first-up. He was placed in a strong 2YO race at this track and distance second-up last preparation before going on to run second in a G3 over 1400m. He's an obvious threat. STRONG MINDED (5) is a lightly-raced 5YO that is learning his craft and is sure to win one of these soon. He can run a cheeky race here. The two Lynch runners ON TIK (3) and FRONTPOINT (1) both have knockout claims at a price.
